<section xml:id="getting-matlab">
	<title>Installing MATLAB</title>

	<p>
		Below are the instructions for installing and/or updating MATLAB. The current version of MATLAB is R2025b. 	
		<ul>
			<li>Go to <url href="https://www.mathworks.com/">Mathworks.com</url></li>
			<li>Click on <q>Sign In</q> (top-right)</li>
			<li>If you don't have one already, create a mathworks account. Use your VMI email address when you do.</li>
			<li>Click on <q>MATLAB</q> (top-right)</li>
			<li>Click on <q>Install MATLAB</q> (top-right)</li>
			<li>Select your operating system in the dropdown menu.</li>
			<li>Save the installer to your computer and launch it after the download completes.</li>
			<li>After it finishes unzipping everything, enter the VMI email and password you used to create a Mathworks account above.</li>
			<li>Accept the licensing agreement.</li>
			<li>Your VMI issued license should be displayed. Select it and click <q>Next</q>.</li>
			<li>Select an installing location (the default is fine) and click <q>Next</q>.</li>
			<li>Use the pre-selected products and click <q>Next</q>.</li>
			<li>Select whether you want a desktop shortcut and whether you want MATLAB to collect your user data.</li>
			<li>Finally, click <q>Begin Install</q>.</li>
			<li>You should now have a copy of MATLAB installed on your Computer.</li>
		</ul>
	</p>
	
</section>